{
  "texts": [
    "Smart homeIn many indoor scenarios, it is expected that the electronic devices can interact with people and monitor the indoor environment to create a comfortable and safe living condition [13].",
    "To achieve this goal, the electronic devices should be able to sense the human activities and the environment in an accurate and timely manner.",
    "Moreover, for the purpose of privacy protection, standard wireless communication signals, such as WiFi [144,145] and 5G New Radio [146], can be modified for the additional sensing capabilities.",
    "For example, Li et al. [144] proposed a positioning method based on WiFi signals, which achieved a positioning accuracy below 0.6 meter.",
    "Xie et al. [145] developed a WiFi tracking system, which fused multi-dimensional information to improve the accuracy."
  ]
}